    "body": "Hi there, thanks for reaching out. \r\nI've tried your code example and I can't get the behaviour you're describing. https://codesandbox.io/s/zen-yonath-xtouu?file=/src/app.js\r\n\r\nI've looked at the codesandbox you provided. I see the issue and for me, it's not quite what you've described. \r\n\r\nIt's related to the fact the new value of type is based on its previous value (see my screenshot). \r\nThis is because `transformItems` writes to the state and can receive already transformed items (this is a known problem tracked by https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/4819). \r\n\r\nFrom what I see on your codesandbox, it's not failing silently, it's just that the templating engine (Hogan) can manage `undefined` values (by showing nothing). \r\n\r\nThe workaround you have is the one I would go for in the meantime.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2982512/129706911-6d890981-acd0-4903-ae38-199b5f28ea7a.png)\r\n\r\nClosing this as a duplicate of #4819 \r\n",
